    "id": 6876143,
    "parent_id": 4626973,
    "root_id": 3599122,
    "comment": "@axat1794, repainting means that you see a buy or sell signal in live trading first and after a while it disappears. This can happen if the candle suddenly turns from red into green. If a candle is closed and the buy or sell signal stays permanent usually it doesn't repaint any more and you can possibly still go into that trade with the next candle (do some backtesting before). If you want to check if a signal repaints, write down the time you see it and late check if it is still there or not.\r\n\nThe creator of this indicator says it doesn't repaint. I haven't tested it yet.",
    "comment_ast": {
      "type": "root",
      "children": [
        {
          "type": "user",
          "params": {
            "link": "/u/axat1794/",
            "name": "axat1794"
          }
        },
        ", repainting means that you see a buy or sell signal in live trading first and after a while it disappears. This can happen if the candle suddenly turns from red into green. If a candle is closed and the buy or sell signal stays permanent usually it doesn't repaint any more and you can possibly still go into that trade with the next candle (do some backtesting before). If you want to check if a signal repaints, write down the time you see it and late check if it is still there or not.\r\n\nThe creator of this indicator says it doesn't repaint. I haven't tested it yet."
      ]
    },
